138612705.review:
Again, I finally end my suffer from this 2.5 D power point model resident evil game. However, unlike resident evil 0 or other games in the Franchise, I pretty much enjoy this one. This is a typical resident evil series that you: 

1. Find you somewhere inside a mansion, a ship, a house or a village;
2. You encounter monsters that being infected by T-virus, G-virus, etc..;
3. You are tracking your partners and solving puzzles  
4. Eventually you end up in a lab and know this is T-virus, G or whatever;
5. You fight the final Boss, sometimes it is wisker, or it is Eveline or it is Amadan...;

I have to be honest that I cannot really enjoy this 2.5 D PPT tank shooting zombie mode although I am 
very good at TPS in following series especially in original RE4, 7, 8 etc.. Therefore, the way to skip this kind
of annoying Tank shooting zombie mode in this one is to start a trainer:

1. Open infinite save; 
2. Get a gun with infinite ammo; 
3. Open a step-by-step walk through, so you do not waste your precious time wondering in this
mansion and then find out "Oh, I forgot pick up that key item that is not that obviously" !

Overall, with the trainer to skip those out-dated part, it is a fun game. I would say it is a downgraded 
RE7 where downgraded is in terms of "game fighting mechanism".

However, if you are a really fan plus endless pointless free time, you can try beat the game in its original, but I highly assume you will be mad at some point, because remember, you can only hear not see animal in certain darn scenarios.

132172693.review:
Resident Evil 1 is a great game even 25 years after the release.  This remastered version still gives a pleasant experience today and runs great on steam deck as well.  The only flaw probably is the direction control especially when switching camera.  My character has been running in circles several times due to this issue and it could be frustrating at times.

Achievements in this games requires several runs.  There are several challenging achievements such as speed run 3 hours,  real survivor mode and CQC FTW.  

I played in the sequence below:
1st and 2nd run:  Chris and Jill each run on low difficulty and get best endings;
3rd run:  Jill No save run on very easy;
4th run:  Jill 3 hours speed run on normal;
5th run:  Jill real survival run, it will get you hard difficulty achievement at the same time;
6th run:  Chris CQC FTW and invisible enemy at the same time on very easy.
If you are familiar with the game, some of the runs can be combined, but a minimum of 4 runs are required for all achievements.
